main event: A round, cylindrical, bright white object was observed in the sky over Menlo Park, California on September 7, 1965.
interesting points: The object was at an altitude of approximately 2000 feet and was observed for a few seconds.
The object moved in a straight, level trajectory from north to south.
The sighting was reported by a civilian ground observer.
A similar sighting was reported at NAS Norfolk, but it was evaluated as not being a threat due to the time and location.
The weather conditions were clear with 15 mile visibility.
sighted object: a round, cylindrical, bright white object
